      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef check_permission(user, resource, action):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns True if user can perform action on resource.\n    Rules:\n    1. 'owner' can do anything.\n    2. 'admin' can do anything.\n    3. 'manager' can 'edit' or 'view'.\n    4. 'editor' can only 'view'.\n    5. 'viewer' can only 'view'.\n    \"\"\"\n    if user.role == \"owner\":\n        return True\n    if user.role == \"admin\":\n        return True\n    if user.role == \"manager\":\n        return action in [\"edit\", \"view\"]\n    if user.role == \"editor\":\n        return action == \"view\"\n    if user.role == \"viewer\":\n        return action == \"view\"\n    return False\n```\nThis function checks the user's role and compares it to the required role for the resource and the action being performed. If the user's role is the same as the required role, or if the user is an admin, they can perform the action. Otherwise, they can only view if they are an editor or viewer.",
